WEBVTT

00:00:28.328 --> 00:00:30.139
va agar bitta ayol bo'lsa,

00:00:30.139 --> 00:00:31.945
biz uni 'woman' deymiz.

00:00:31.945 --> 00:00:33.848
Bitta g'oz — 'goose',

00:00:33.848 --> 00:00:35.090
ko'plikda esa — 'geese'.

00:00:35.090 --> 00:00:37.555
Lekin bitta los — 'moose' bo'lsa,
nega ko'plikda

00:00:37.555 --> 00:00:39.259
'meese' emas?
Agar ikkita oyoq —

00:00:39.259 --> 00:00:41.429
'feet' bo'lsa,
nega ko'p kitoblarni biz

00:00:41.429 --> 00:00:43.512
'beek' demaymiz?

00:00:43.512 --> 00:00:45.313
Aslida biz 1000 yil oldingi

00:00:45.313 --> 00:00:47.656
ingliz tilida gaplashganimizda,

00:00:47.656 --> 00:00:49.662
kitoblarni ko'plikda o'zi

00:00:49.662 --> 00:00:51.531
'beek' degan bo'lardik.

00:00:51.531 --> 00:00:53.451
Zamonaviy ingliz tili g'alati bo'lsa,

00:00:53.451 --> 00:00:55.286
eski ingliz tili esa umuman aqldan

00:00:55.286 --> 00:00:56.354
ozdiradi.
Ishonasizmi,

00:00:56.354 --> 00:00:58.546
o'sha paytlardagi ingliz tili 
o'rganish uchun

00:00:58.546 --> 00:01:01.048
hozirgidanam qiyinroq bo'lgan.